A cozy evening scene in Studio Ghibli style: a father sits in a plush armchair with two young twin boys nestled on either side of him, all three bathed in warm lamplight. An open book rests across his lap, pages softly glowing. The children lean in with wide, wonder-filled eyes, their expressions showing complete absorption in the story. Around them, wisps of imagination materialize into the air—subtle magical swirls and faint ethereal shapes suggesting adventure and mystery floating upward from the book's pages. The room is warmly lit with deep shadows in the corners, scattered books on nearby shelves, and a soft blanket draped over the chair. The scene radiates intimacy, curiosity, and the sacred bond of shared storytelling between parent and children.
